## Basic Usage
- Use className prop instead of StyleSheet for styling (className="bg-blue-500 p-4")
- Create consistent spacing with p-[number] and m-[number] classes
- Implement responsive layouts with flex, justify, and items classes
- Use dark: prefix for dark mode styling (className="bg-white dark:bg-black")
- Avoid inline styles when NativeWind classes would work

## Best Practices
- Group related styles into reusable className strings for consistency
- Add tw-prefixed comments above complex className strings to explain intent
- Use dynamic classes with template literals for conditional styling

## Configuration
- Configure babel plugin in babel.config.js
- Extend theme in tailwind.config.js for custom design system elements
- Add custom utilities in tailwind.config.js as needed

## Advanced Usage
- Create custom variants for platform-specific styling
- Use NativeWind plugins for advanced functionality
- Configure content paths in tailwind.config.js to match project structure
- Setup proper type definitions with typescript
- Optimize compilation with babel plugin options

## Troubleshooting
- Rebuild app if style changes aren't reflected
- Check configuration if className strings aren't applying
- Refer to NativeWind docs for version-specific features
